**Mn_9.62** is the verse: once the purpose of the *niyoga* appointment is fulfilled (the son is born), the widow and her husband's brother must henceforth treat each other as daughter-in-law and guru — the appointed relationship ends, and any continuation out of lust makes both outcastes (Mn_9.63).
